text:
Hey everyone sorry for the slight drop off... because of how well things seemed to be progressing for him, my adrenaline completely fell off the cliff.  I guess after 3-4 months of staying up and watching / trying to catch each attack and suppress it with O2, I managed to get hit with the big ole exhaustion and spent a few days completely fatigued.
The
GOOD
news is.... I don't want to call it just yet because I normally wait a solid 2-3 weeks before calling it but since Bust #2 he hasn't had any pain or shadows since that first day. It's been a really nice run of 10-12 days of peace of no pain and no shadows..
I remember
@spiny
once saying
"once you know / you know"
in reference to judging whether a cycle is over and he feels like it's gone - based on his 21 years of gutfeel and experience. There's a chance we busted just as the cycle was on its way out but I firmly believe it helped nudge this particularly stubborn one out the door faster. There were very clear indications eg. 24 hours after Bust 1 the pain went / shadows persisted. After Bust 2 no pain / no shadows after 48 hours. As a result and in the interests of preserving the last bit of medicine, he feels he can get away with not having to do the third bust.
I'm waiting another week or so to officially call the cycle definitely over but wanted to give you all an update.
I REALLY don't know how to thank you all especially
@spiny
@Bejeeber
@Shaun brearley
@CHfather
@snafu
@xBoss
@jon019
... I came here at the start of the month completely broken and terrified and you all selflessly contributed your wisdom and time, leapt in and guided me through all this - especially those harrowing days of detoxing from sumatriptan and opioids. To say you had a hand in saving a life over here would be an understatement - I sincerely mean this as we were at our wits end... we are so eternally grateful. I hope I can work out a permanent solution for him so I can jump on here and contribute materially and positively as we see more newbie posters here, having been in the exact situation myself time and time again and being so heartbroken that nothing ever worked for him for 21 years.
Assuming the next week is safe sailing, I think my focus is now to putting together a plan of attack.
I wanted to ask:
Long term storage of Vitamin L -
@spiny
I think you mentioned the freezer / wrapped in foil / in an airtight box? I imagine I would need to cut it up into individual doses but one thing I was unclear on was in the event we had to use, do we wait for it to come to room temperature (and if so, wouldn't there be condensation / compromises the potency?).
Maintenance Dosing of Vitamin L - I think
@Shaun brearley
has an approach of "maintenance dose regardless of symptoms or not' but would you mind sharing the details? If anyone else has a maintenance dose guide of what they do that would be amazing= (I think
@xBoss
